Polymorphism is an OOP concept where one entity takes multiple forms. In Java it is achieved through method overloading (compile time) and method overriding (runtime).

Polymorphism means "one thing, many forms". Same action performed differently by different objects.

Polymorphism
│
├── Compile Time (Static)
│   └── Method Overloading
│       → Same class
│       → Same name
│       → Different parameters
│       → Decided at compile time
│
└── Runtime (Dynamic)
    └── Method Overriding
        → Parent-Child class
        → Same name
        → Same parameters
        → Decided at runtime